WEBVTT

00:35.536 --> 00:37.070
[ Hermes ]
EXCITING NEWS,
PEOPLE!

00:37.170 --> 00:40.307
THE PET LICENSE
I REQUISITIONED FOR
NIBBLER HAS ARRIVED.

00:40.408 --> 00:41.609
HERMES, THAT'S SWEET.

00:41.709 --> 00:43.944
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU CARED ABOUT NIBBLER.

00:44.043 --> 00:45.279
DREAM ON, WOMAN.

00:45.378 --> 00:47.314
I'D LIKE TO PUT
THE LITTLE BASTARD IN A SACK

00:47.414 --> 00:50.250
AND TOSS THE SACK IN A RIVER
AND HURL THE RIVER INTO SPACE

00:50.350 --> 00:52.119
BUT I DO LIKE
FILLING OUT REQUISITIONS

00:52.219 --> 00:55.155
AND THESE WERE SOME DOOZIES.

00:55.256 --> 00:58.491
GREAT JAH'S DREADLOCKS!
THERE'S BEEN A MIX-UP.

00:58.591 --> 01:02.162
THIS ISN'T A PET LICENSE,
IT'S A FISHING LICENSE!

01:02.262 --> 01:03.996
AND IT'S MANDATORY!

01:16.644 --> 01:20.248
[ Farnsworth ]
AH! THE EXACT CENTER
OF THE ATLANTIC OCEAN.

01:20.347 --> 01:23.082
THIS SEEMS THE LOGICAL PLACE
FOR FISH TO CONGREGATE.

01:23.183 --> 01:24.817
SO, WE'RE
IN INTERNATIONAL WATERS?

01:24.918 --> 01:26.686
INDEED SO.

01:26.787 --> 01:29.923
FALCON, THIS IS BLUE RAVEN.
THE GOOSE HAS NESTED.

01:30.022 --> 01:31.992
REPEAT, THE GOOSE HAS NESTED.

01:35.996 --> 01:38.698
HEY, GUESS WHAT
YOU'RE ACCESSORIES TO.

01:38.799 --> 01:42.170
THE SUN, THE SEA AIR,
GOOD FRIENDS...

01:42.270 --> 01:43.637
LEELA'S RIGHT.
FISHING BLOWS.

01:43.736 --> 01:45.673
WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE MAKE IT INTERESTING?

01:45.772 --> 01:47.307
[ Acknowledging Comments ]

01:47.408 --> 01:50.677
EVERYBODY KICK IN FIVE BUCKS.

01:50.777 --> 01:52.646
THERE, WASN'T THAT INTERESTING?

01:52.746 --> 01:54.814
- BENDER!
- [ Chuckles ]

01:54.914 --> 01:56.549
THIS CONTEST IS
AS GOOD AS OVER.

01:56.650 --> 01:59.019
I ONCE CAUGHT
A FISH THIS BIG.

01:59.118 --> 02:00.287
OH, YEAH?

02:00.388 --> 02:02.555
I ONCE CAUGHT A FISH
THIS BIG.

02:03.990 --> 02:05.992
I'M AFRAID YOU'RE
BOTH OUT OF YOUR
LEAGUE, BOYS

02:06.093 --> 02:09.562
'CAUSE YOU'RE LOOKING AT A WOMAN
WHO OWNS HER OWN HARPOON.

02:09.663 --> 02:11.831
HARPOON, MY ASS.
[ Chuckles ]

02:11.931 --> 02:13.834
OKAY.
[ Yells ]

02:13.933 --> 02:17.837
LET'S SEE NOW.
WHICH BAIT TO USE...

02:17.937 --> 02:20.039
CRICKETS, SQUID

02:20.139 --> 02:23.644
CHICKEN NECKS?
EXCUSE ME.
IF I MIGHT BE SO BOLD,

02:23.743 --> 02:27.514
I'M WILLING TO OFFER
MY SERVICES AS A BAIT CRITIC.

02:27.615 --> 02:29.349
THESE SARDINES,
FOR EXAMPLE

02:29.449 --> 02:31.084
ARE BLAND AND TASTELESS.

02:31.185 --> 02:33.353
[ Gobbling Noisily ]

02:33.454 --> 02:36.022
AND THESE DRY,
STRINGY NIGHT CRAWLERS--

02:36.122 --> 02:40.360
THOUGH JUICY...
VERY, VERY JUICY...

02:40.461 --> 02:43.864
[ Obnoxious Slurping ]

02:43.963 --> 02:46.366
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS!
IT'S EATING MY BAIT!

02:46.466 --> 02:48.201
BEAT IT,
YOU MOOCHING CRAWDAD!

02:48.301 --> 02:52.171
[ Imitating Curly ]
WOO, WOO, WOO, WOO, WOO!

02:52.272 --> 02:54.074
[ Sonar Beeping ]

02:54.174 --> 02:57.510
HEY, FRY, CHECK OUT
MY LASER-GUIDED
FISHING ROD.

02:57.610 --> 02:59.780
QUIET, BENDER,
YOU'RE SCARING AWAY THE FISH.

02:59.879 --> 03:02.515
FINE. I'LL HEAD OVER
TO THE OTHER SIDE.

03:02.616 --> 03:05.752
[ Yelling ]
GOOD LUCK FISHING
ON THIS SIDE!

03:05.853 --> 03:07.520
[ Casting Whir ]

03:07.621 --> 03:08.921
[ Chuckling ]

03:09.021 --> 03:11.391
I CAN HIT A FISH
BETWEEN THE EYES FROM 20 YARDS.

03:11.491 --> 03:13.961
OH, YEAH?
I CAN HIT A SHRIMP.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.462
A SHRIMP?
[ Casting Whir ]

03:15.562 --> 03:17.197
I FIND IT A BIT HARD
TO BELIEVE THAT...

03:17.298 --> 03:20.199
[ Fry Grunts ]
AH, HA!

03:20.300 --> 03:23.069
GATHER 'ROUND, CHUMPS.

03:23.170 --> 03:24.604
I GOT THE WINNER!

03:25.906 --> 03:27.240
OH...

03:27.341 --> 03:31.211
OH, SO THIS IS WHERE
YOU SHOP FOR YOUR BOOTS.

03:31.312 --> 03:32.812
[ Bender ]
COUPLE MORE OF THOSE

03:32.913 --> 03:34.948
AND YOU'LL HAVE
YOURSELF A FISH STICK.

03:35.048 --> 03:37.784
[ Hearty Laughter ]
HEY!

03:37.884 --> 03:40.554
A FISH THIS FINE BELONGS
IN A FISH-NUGGET-STYLE CHUNKLET.

03:40.653 --> 03:43.390
ANYWAY, IT'S BIGGER
THAN ANYTHING YOU'VE CAUGHT.

03:43.490 --> 03:44.625
[ Chuckles ]

03:44.724 --> 03:45.992
[ Casting Whir ]

03:46.093 --> 03:48.329
[ Fry ]
OW! MY SMALL INTESTINE!

03:48.429 --> 03:50.663
[ Grunts ]
[ Splash ]

03:50.764 --> 03:52.064
BINGO!

03:52.164 --> 03:55.502
WHATEVER IT IS, IT'S 20 TIMES
HEAVIER THAN A BOOT.

03:57.670 --> 04:00.741
OH!
YOU'LL NEVER
CATCH ANYTHING

04:00.841 --> 04:02.409
WITH THAT
PRIMITIVE TECHNOLOGY.

04:02.509 --> 04:05.111
WHAT YOU NEED
IS THIS FISH PHEROMONE--

04:05.211 --> 04:08.515
THE MOST POTENT APHRODISIAC
KNOWN TO FISHKIND.

04:08.615 --> 04:11.284
[ Rattling ]

04:11.384 --> 04:12.520
UH, OH.

04:12.620 --> 04:15.122
[ Yelling ]

04:15.222 --> 04:16.456
[ Sniffing ]

04:16.557 --> 04:19.326
I'MINTO YOU.

04:19.427 --> 04:21.329
[ Slurping ]

04:21.428 --> 04:23.831
OH, MY!

04:23.930 --> 04:25.298
[ Whirring ]

04:25.399 --> 04:26.466
HEY, BENDER!

04:26.567 --> 04:28.369
I JUST CAUGHT A FISH
THIS BIG.

04:28.468 --> 04:30.437
QUIT EXAGGERATING, FRY.

04:30.538 --> 04:32.706
AW, SCREW THIS.

04:32.805 --> 04:34.841
IF I'M NOT GOING
TO CATCH A FISH

04:34.942 --> 04:37.144
I MIGHT AS WELL NOT CATCH
A BIG FISH.

04:37.244 --> 04:38.346
[ Metal Creaking ]

04:38.446 --> 04:39.480
THERE.

04:39.579 --> 04:40.980
LIKE MOST OF LIFE'S PROBLEMS

04:41.081 --> 04:42.816
THIS ONE CAN BE SOLVED
WITH BENDING.

04:44.651 --> 04:46.319
BENDER, BE CAREFUL!

04:46.420 --> 04:48.988
THAT'S THE SHIP'S
DIAMOND FILAMENT TETHER.

04:49.088 --> 04:50.457
IT'S UNBREAKABLE.

04:50.557 --> 04:52.192
THEN WHY DO I
HAVE TO BE CAREFUL?

04:52.292 --> 04:55.062
IT BELONGED TO MY GRANDMOTHER.

04:55.161 --> 04:57.331
[ Grunts ]

04:57.430 --> 04:58.499
[ Splash ]

04:58.598 --> 05:00.500
MY MANWICH!

05:03.170 --> 05:05.473
[ All Snoring ]

05:11.011 --> 05:12.346
[ Squeaking ]

05:12.446 --> 05:14.382
[ Splash ]

05:14.481 --> 05:15.716
WAKE UP, EVERYONE!

05:15.815 --> 05:18.351
I'VE GOT SOMETHING,
AND THIS TIME IT'S ALIVE.

05:21.321 --> 05:25.324
OH! DR. ZOIDBERG,
SINCE WHEN DO YOU
EVEN WEAR BOOTS?

05:25.425 --> 05:26.894
I WASN'T WEARING IT.

05:26.994 --> 05:28.829
I WAS EATING IT.

05:28.928 --> 05:30.764
[ Groan And Splash ]

05:30.863 --> 05:32.899
COME ON, LET'S GO HOME.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.334
[ Screams ]

05:34.435 --> 05:35.502
SUNBURN!

05:35.603 --> 05:37.004
MY FABULOUS BODY!

05:37.103 --> 05:38.170
IT'S RUINED!

05:38.271 --> 05:39.673
WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY PARASOL?

05:39.773 --> 05:40.841
I DON'T KNOW.

05:40.941 --> 05:43.009
IT WASN'T HERE
WHEN I TOOK YOUR UMBRELLA.

05:43.110 --> 05:44.276
WHAT?!

05:44.377 --> 05:45.946
I PUT SUNBLOCK ON YOU.

05:46.045 --> 05:48.548
WELL, IT DIDN'T WORK.

05:48.649 --> 05:49.850
[ Sinister Chuckle ]

05:49.949 --> 05:51.685
[ Leela ]
COME ON, BENDER.

05:51.784 --> 05:54.521
PULL IN YOUR LINE,
AND LET'S GO.

05:54.622 --> 05:56.856
[ Metal Squeaking ]

05:56.956 --> 05:58.425
[ Grunts ]

05:58.526 --> 06:01.261
HEY, I'M SNAGGED.

06:01.360 --> 06:02.463
IT'S NOT SNAGGED.

06:02.562 --> 06:04.697
THE MECHANO-MAN
HAS CAUGHT SOMETHING.

06:04.798 --> 06:05.798
[ Grunting ]

06:09.769 --> 06:13.574
SWEET ZOMBIE JESUS!
IT'S HUGE!

06:13.673 --> 06:14.807
IT'S COMING UP!

06:20.781 --> 06:21.949
[ Gasping And Yelling ]

06:22.048 --> 06:25.718
WHOA, THAT'S BIG!
A COLOSSAL MOUTH BASS!

06:27.319 --> 06:28.822
[ Whirring Accelerating ]

06:28.922 --> 06:30.122
IT'S DIVING!

06:30.223 --> 06:31.725
[ Metal Groaning ]

06:31.824 --> 06:34.326
IT'S PULLING US UNDER!
EVERYONE, INTO THE SHIP!

06:34.427 --> 06:36.062
WAIT, I'LL SAVE US...

06:36.163 --> 06:38.899
BY CUTTING THE UNBREAKABLE
DIAMOND FILAMENT.

06:38.999 --> 06:40.332
[ Groaning ]

06:40.433 --> 06:43.603
WELL, AT LEAST I'LL DIE
WITH MY FRIENDS.

06:43.704 --> 06:44.771
HELLO?

06:44.872 --> 06:46.473
[ Clank ]

06:50.143 --> 06:53.947
[ All Screaming ]

06:54.047 --> 06:55.983
[ Hermes ]
MY SPEEDOS!

07:02.822 --> 07:05.526
[ Alarm Blaring ]
DEPTH AT 45 HUNDRED FEET...

07:05.625 --> 07:08.028
48 HUNDRED,
50 HUNDRED...

07:08.127 --> 07:09.797
5,000 FEET.

07:09.896 --> 07:10.963
DEAR LORD!

07:11.064 --> 07:13.500
THAT'S OVER 150 ATMOSPHERES
OF PRESSURE!

07:13.600 --> 07:16.302
HOW MANY ATMOSPHERES
CAN THE SHIP WITHSTAND?

07:16.403 --> 07:17.670
WELL, IT'S A SPACESHIP

07:17.771 --> 07:20.339
SO I'D SAY ANYWHERE
BETWEEN ZERO AND ONE.

07:20.439 --> 07:22.009
[ Metal Groaning ]

07:22.108 --> 07:25.278
WHAT'S THAT?
IS SOMEONE BENDING GIRDERS?

07:25.377 --> 07:27.113
[ Creaking And Groaning ]

07:29.483 --> 07:30.983
OY!

07:32.384 --> 07:34.622
WE'LL BE CRUSHED IF WE DON'T
EQUALIZE THE PRESSURE.

07:34.721 --> 07:36.723
HOW DO WE DO THAT?

07:36.824 --> 07:38.492
THAT SHOULD DO IT.

07:38.591 --> 07:40.159
OH! WE'RE ALL GOING TO DIE!

07:40.259 --> 07:42.896
WAIT, I'LL BE BACK IN A MINUTE.

07:42.995 --> 07:44.697
[ Loud Flush ]

07:51.471 --> 07:52.673
[ Cheering ]

07:52.773 --> 07:55.007
- YOU DID IT, FRY!
- DID WHAT?

07:55.108 --> 07:56.709
[ Explosive Thud ]

07:56.810 --> 07:57.677
[ Yelling ]

07:57.778 --> 08:00.346
[ Metal Groaning ]

08:02.048 --> 08:04.817
PEOPLE, IT'S FAR, FAR WORSE

08:04.918 --> 08:06.019
THAN WE THOUGHT.

08:06.119 --> 08:08.321
MY FISH GOT AWAY.

08:08.420 --> 08:09.923
[ Electrical Crackling ]

08:11.591 --> 08:12.826
THERE! GOOD AS NEW.

08:12.925 --> 08:15.427
EXCEPT THAT WE'RE
THREE MILES BELOW THE SURFACE

08:15.528 --> 08:16.663
WE DON'T HAVE ANY FOOD

08:16.764 --> 08:18.699
AND THE SHIP WON'T WORK
UNDERWATER.

08:18.798 --> 08:20.701
TEMPERS
ARE WEARING THIN.

08:20.800 --> 08:24.004
LET'S JUST HOPE SOME ROBOT
DOESN'T KILL EVERYBODY.

08:24.103 --> 08:26.338
THE IMPORTANT THING
IS THAT WE DON'T PANIC.

08:26.439 --> 08:29.042
THERE ARE RULES
FOR SITUATIONS LIKE THIS.

08:29.141 --> 08:31.411
NOW, THE FIRST ORDER OF BUSINESS
IS LUNCH.

08:31.511 --> 08:34.514
I SUGGEST
A NICE LOBSTER ZOIDBERG.

08:34.615 --> 08:35.783
I MEAN, UH,
LOBSTER NEWBURG.

08:35.883 --> 08:37.884
I MEAN,
DR. ZOIDBERG.

08:37.985 --> 08:39.886
OKAY, EVERYONE.
CALM DOWN.

08:39.986 --> 08:42.623
THE PROFESSOR AND I
WILL GET TO WORK
ON THE SHIP.

08:42.722 --> 08:45.424
BENDER, ZOIDBERG,
SINCE YOU CAN
SURVIVE UNDERWATER

08:45.524 --> 08:47.126
YOU'LL GO OUT
AND LOOK FOR FOOD.

08:47.226 --> 08:48.360
I BETTER GO, TOO.

08:48.461 --> 08:49.763
THEY DON'T KNOW WHAT I LIKE.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.463
FRY, NO! THE PRESSURE
WILL CRUSH YOU

08:51.565 --> 08:53.567
LIKE A GREEN SNAKE
UNDER A SUGARCANE TRUCK!

08:53.667 --> 08:54.735
NOT NECESSARILY.

08:54.835 --> 08:57.303
THIS IS A CHANCE
FOR FRY TO TEST OUT

08:57.403 --> 08:59.740
MY EXPERIMENTAL
ANTI-PRESSURE PILL.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.808
I CAN'T
SWALLOW THAT.

09:01.908 --> 09:03.442
WELL, THEN, GOOD NEWS!

09:03.543 --> 09:05.477
IT'S A SUPPOSITORY.

09:09.548 --> 09:11.551
HOW ARE
YOU DOING THERE, FRY?

09:11.652 --> 09:13.653
[ Gurgling ]

09:15.054 --> 09:16.956
GLAD TO HEAR IT.

09:17.057 --> 09:18.958
AHA!

09:19.058 --> 09:20.793
[ Grunts ]

09:22.929 --> 09:25.765
[ Voice Vibrating ]
AW, YEAH!

09:25.865 --> 09:29.501
YUM, YUM, YUM.

09:31.337 --> 09:32.806
UH-OH.

09:32.905 --> 09:34.607
[ Imitating Three Stooges ]

09:37.476 --> 09:38.645
LOOK AT ME.

09:38.745 --> 09:42.481
I'M DR. ZOIDBERG--
HOMEOWNER.

09:47.019 --> 09:48.087
CAREFUL, FRY.

09:48.187 --> 09:50.322
I THINK THAT FLAG
MIGHT BE POISONOUS.

09:50.423 --> 09:51.658
AHOY, MATEYS!

09:51.759 --> 09:54.193
I SHANGHAIED US
SOME HEARTY GRUB.

09:54.293 --> 09:56.296
[ Pops ]

09:58.331 --> 09:59.767
[ Growls ]

09:59.866 --> 10:03.370
THE LAWS OF SCIENCE
BE A HARSH MISTRESS.

10:03.470 --> 10:06.974
SAY, ROBOT, OLD BUDDY,
COULD YOU HELP ME MOVE A COUCH?

10:07.073 --> 10:10.610
AW, OKAY, BUT I'M NOT
CARRYING IT UPSTAIRS.

10:17.283 --> 10:18.317
[ Gasps ]

10:18.418 --> 10:19.720
[ Giggling ]

10:21.288 --> 10:23.724
[ Gurgling Incoherently ]

10:23.823 --> 10:24.825
WHAT IS IT, FRY?

10:24.924 --> 10:26.793
[ Still Gurgling ]
...ADE.

10:26.894 --> 10:29.328
YOU WANT SOME LEMONADE?
YOU SAW A BIG PARADE?

10:29.428 --> 10:31.498
YOUR STUDENTS LOANS
HAVE BEEN REPAID?

10:31.597 --> 10:34.167
THEN HOW ABOUT LENDING
YOUR OLD PAL ZOIDBERG

10:34.267 --> 10:36.568
A FEW BUCKS, MR. MILLIONAIRE?

10:36.669 --> 10:38.304
[ Fry Speaking Incoherently ]

10:41.408 --> 10:43.744
FRY, SWALLOW YOUR FOOD,
THEN TALK.

10:43.844 --> 10:45.577
[ Gulps Noisily ]

10:45.678 --> 10:47.014
A MERMAID!

10:47.114 --> 10:49.515
YOU THINK YOU
SAW A MERMAID?

10:49.615 --> 10:52.351
NO. I DID SEE A MERMAID.
SHE WAS WEARING A TUBE TOP.

10:52.451 --> 10:54.486
AND SHE HAD
A BEAUTIFUL, SCALY TAIL

10:54.586 --> 10:56.489
AND I THINK SHE HAD
HAIR EXTENSIONS.

10:56.588 --> 10:58.158
[ Disbelieving Comments ]

10:58.258 --> 11:01.660
YOU'RE SIMPLY
HALLUCINATING,
YOU MORON.

11:01.761 --> 11:03.831
WHAT'S SO
FAR-FETCHED
ABOUT MERMAIDS?

11:03.931 --> 11:06.033
THERE'S ALL SORTS
OF WEIRD SEA CREATURES

11:06.133 --> 11:08.534
HERE IN THE FUTURE,
LIKE DR. ZOIDBERG.

11:11.403 --> 11:13.941
I'M AFRAID FRY IS
SUFFERING FROM
OCEAN MADNESS.

11:14.041 --> 11:16.176
EVERY TIME SOMETHING GOOD
HAPPENS TO ME

11:16.275 --> 11:18.677
YOU SAY IT'S SOME KIND
OF MADNESS OR I'M DRUNK

11:18.778 --> 11:19.913
OR I ATE TOO MUCH CANDY.

11:20.013 --> 11:21.347
WELL, I SAW A REAL MERMAID

11:21.447 --> 11:23.682
AND I WISH JUST ONCE
MY FRIENDS WOULD HAVE

11:23.783 --> 11:25.753
THE DECENCY AND KINDNESS
TO BELIEVE ME.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.888
OCEAN MADNESS.

11:27.988 --> 11:29.288
[ Slams ]

11:29.389 --> 11:31.423
HE MAY HAVE OCEAN MADNESS

11:31.524 --> 11:34.193
BUT THAT'S NO EXCUSE
FOR OCEAN RUDENESS.

11:36.897 --> 11:41.067
[ Snoring ]

11:41.168 --> 11:43.269
"OCEAN MADNESS."
YEAH, RIGHT.

11:43.370 --> 11:46.105
YEAH, IT'S ALWAYS SOMETHING,
AIN'T IT?

11:46.206 --> 11:48.207
[ Gasping ]
IT'S HER!

11:48.307 --> 11:50.110
BENDER, WAKE UP!
SHE'S HERE! WAKE UP!

11:50.210 --> 11:51.577
[ Snoring ]

11:51.677 --> 11:53.580
[ Very Loud Snoring ]

11:55.282 --> 11:56.716
[ Gulps ]

11:56.817 --> 11:57.918
OXYGEN.

12:03.655 --> 12:06.658
[ Bubbly Screaming ]

12:06.759 --> 12:09.662
HERE YOU GO,
DARLING.
[ Gasping ]

12:09.763 --> 12:13.133
HEY, I CAN BREATHE.
AND TALK. JUST LIKE A FISH.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.466
OH, YOU SPEAK FISH?

12:14.567 --> 12:17.504
- [ High-pitched Gurgling ]
- WHAT?

12:17.604 --> 12:20.506
I'M SORRY, MY
ACCENT'S ATROCIOUS.

12:20.606 --> 12:23.911
HI. MY NAME'S UMBRIEL.
I'M FRY.

12:24.010 --> 12:25.913
SO, UH,
AM I GOING TO DROWN?

12:26.013 --> 12:28.014
'COURSE NOT.
JUST STAY CALM,

12:28.115 --> 12:30.317
AND LET THE GENTLE CURRENTS
RELAX YOUR EVERY MUSCLE.

12:30.417 --> 12:33.253
OH, YEAH!

12:33.352 --> 12:34.988
DID IT JUST GET WARMER?

12:35.087 --> 12:37.124
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE REALLY REAL.

12:37.224 --> 12:38.191
I LIKE YOUR TAIL.

12:38.290 --> 12:39.625
OH, YOU'RE SWEET.

12:39.725 --> 12:42.495
I LIKE THOSE WIGGLY DOODADS
COMING OUT OF YOUR HIPS.

12:42.595 --> 12:43.495
OH, THANKS.

12:43.596 --> 12:44.496
THEY'RE CALLED PANTS.

12:44.596 --> 12:47.433
THIS HERE'S
A VOLCANIC VENT.

12:47.533 --> 12:50.169
THE WATER COMES OUT
AT OVER 4,000 DEGREES.

12:50.269 --> 12:51.337
NO KIDDING?

12:51.437 --> 12:53.005
AH.

12:53.105 --> 12:55.042
DID IT JUST GET COLDER?

12:56.775 --> 13:00.447
TELL ME MORE ABOUT THAT BIZARRE
LANDY WORLD YOU COME FROM.

13:00.547 --> 13:02.115
IS THERE WATER THERE, TOO?

13:02.215 --> 13:04.484
SURE. SOMETIMES IT
FALLS FROM THE SKY.

13:04.583 --> 13:06.552
HMM.
AND SOMETIMES
IT DOESN'T.

13:06.653 --> 13:08.054
[ Gasping ]

13:08.154 --> 13:09.856
OH, MR. FRY, YOU DO GO ON.

13:09.956 --> 13:12.826
YOU KNOW WHAT I LIKE
BEST ABOUT YOU, UMBRIEL?

13:12.926 --> 13:14.461
YOU FIND ME FASCINATING

13:14.561 --> 13:17.496
EVEN WHEN I'M NOT CLAIMING TO BE
A JEWEL THIEF OR A LION TAMER.

13:17.596 --> 13:20.366
LIONS? THERE ARE SEA LIONS
ON THE LAND?

13:20.466 --> 13:22.836
YUP. WE CALL THEM
"LAND SEA LIONS."

13:22.936 --> 13:24.004
I TAME THEM.

13:52.231 --> 13:53.900
I'M ALMOST DONE
RECONFIGURING

13:54.000 --> 13:56.168
THE SHIP'S
PROPULSION SYSTEM.

13:56.269 --> 13:59.538
WE CAN LEAVE AS SOON AS
THE PAPIER-MÂCHE IS DRY.

13:59.639 --> 14:02.375
- WHERE'S FRY?
- I DIDN'T KILL HIM. PROFESSOR?

14:02.475 --> 14:04.344
NO, I'VE BEEN BUSY.

14:04.443 --> 14:07.246
HE MUST HAVE GONE OUT
LOOKING FOR THAT "MERMAID."

14:07.346 --> 14:09.249
THE POOR, DEMENTED HONKY.

14:09.349 --> 14:11.418
IT'S OCEAN MADNESS, ALL RIGHT.

14:11.518 --> 14:15.187
SAILORS CALL IT "AQUA DEMENTIA,"
"THE DEEP DOWN CRAZIES,"

14:15.288 --> 14:17.957
"THE WET WILLIES,"
"THE SCREAMING MOIST..."

14:18.057 --> 14:19.792
WE'LL FORM A SEARCH PARTY.

14:19.893 --> 14:21.394
NOW, WE'LL NEED OXYGEN.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.529
I GOT IT COVERED.

14:23.629 --> 14:25.097
IN THE EVENT
OF AN EMERGENCY

14:25.197 --> 14:27.533
MY ASS CAN BE USED
AS A FLOTATION DEVICE.

14:27.634 --> 14:28.634
OH, THAT REMINDS ME.

14:28.735 --> 14:31.038
YOU'VE ALL TAKEN YOUR
PRESSURE PILLS, RIGHT?

14:31.138 --> 14:33.240
YES. STOP ASKING.

14:34.740 --> 14:38.811
[ Sniffing ]

14:38.912 --> 14:39.980
I'VE GOT HIS SCENT.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.615
OVER HERE
WHERE THE WATER GETS WARMER.

14:42.715 --> 14:44.051
[ Smacking Lips ]

14:44.150 --> 14:45.418
THIS WAY.

14:48.120 --> 14:49.221
[ All Gasping ]

14:49.322 --> 14:51.457
[ All ]
OOH!

14:52.625 --> 14:54.494
BEND ME!

14:54.594 --> 14:57.230
[ Speaking Chinese ]
DUDE!

14:57.330 --> 14:59.466
AN ANCIENT SUNKEN CITY!

15:01.900 --> 15:05.605
COULD IT POSSIBLY BE?
ARE THE OLD LEGENDS TRUE?

15:08.607 --> 15:10.610
[ Awed Exclamations ]
IT IS!

15:10.710 --> 15:14.581
IT'S THE FABLED
LOST CITY OF ATLANTA!

15:14.681 --> 15:16.249
HOWDY, Y'ALL!

15:19.318 --> 15:20.452
WELCOME TO ATLANTA.

15:20.552 --> 15:23.090
FOLKS 'ROUND THESE PARTS
CALL ME THE COLONEL.

15:23.190 --> 15:26.192
[ Humming Banjo Music ]

15:26.293 --> 15:27.826
HERE, HAVE SOME BREATHERS

15:27.927 --> 15:30.163
COURTESY OF
OUR CHAMBER OF COMMERCE.

15:32.831 --> 15:35.501
THIS IS UNCOMFORTABLE
AND HUMILIATING.

15:35.601 --> 15:39.672
NOW, IF THEY COULD PUT IT
IN THE FORM OF A SUPPOSITORY...

15:39.772 --> 15:41.140
Y'ALL ENJOY YOUR STAY.

15:41.240 --> 15:43.775
TOURISM'S OUR MAIN SOURCE
OF INCOME 'ROUND HERE

15:43.875 --> 15:46.312
SO, UH, SEE THE SIGHTS,
SPEND SOME MONEY...

15:46.413 --> 15:47.480
PLEASE DON'T LEAVE.

15:47.580 --> 15:49.481
[ Bender ]
FRY!

15:49.581 --> 15:51.618
OH, I JUST KNEW
YOU WERE STILL ALIVE!

15:51.717 --> 15:53.286
I OWE YOU TEN BUCKS, HERMES.

15:53.385 --> 15:55.221
HEY, THE MOST
AMAZING THING HAPPENED.

15:55.322 --> 15:58.125
IT'S TWO-FOR-ONE TUESDAY
AT KRISPY KREME

15:58.225 --> 15:59.491
PLUS, THERE'S MERMAIDS.

15:59.591 --> 16:00.826
NICE OUT-OF-TOWN FOLKS

16:00.927 --> 16:03.296
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET
MY DAUGHTER, UMBRIEL.

16:03.395 --> 16:05.664
UMBRIEL, THESE ARE SOME YANKEES.

16:05.764 --> 16:08.067
SO, FRY

16:08.168 --> 16:10.169
ATLANTA WAS AN AMERICAN CITY
IN YOUR TIME?

16:10.269 --> 16:11.870
I THINK IT WAS
JUST AN AIRPORT.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.041
THEY HAD A PLACE WHERE
YOU COULD BUY NUTS.

16:14.140 --> 16:17.809
NO! ANCIENT ATLANTA WAS
MORE THAN JUST A DELTA HUB.

16:17.909 --> 16:22.149
IT WAS A VIBRANT METROPOLIS--
THE EQUAL OF PARIS OR NEW YORK.

16:22.249 --> 16:24.350
THAT'S RIGHT, HONEY.
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

16:24.451 --> 16:26.552
LOOK AT THESE
FABULOUS RUINS--

16:26.653 --> 16:30.822
TURNER FIELD,
THE COCA-COLA BOTTLING PLANT

16:30.923 --> 16:33.025
THE, UH... THE AIRPORT.

16:33.125 --> 16:34.927
BUT, TELL US,
HOW COULD A CITY

16:35.028 --> 16:36.995
WITH SUCH A...
FABULOUS AIRPORT

16:37.096 --> 16:38.331
END UP UNDERWATER?

16:38.431 --> 16:39.831
AH, NOW,
THAT'S A STORY

16:39.932 --> 16:43.102
THAT CAN ONLY RIGHTLY BE TOLD
IN A CHAMBER OF COMMERCE VIDEO

16:43.202 --> 16:45.672
NARRATED BY
FOLK-ROCK TROUBADOUR, DONOVAN.

16:45.772 --> 16:47.340
[ Beeps ]

16:47.440 --> 16:50.043
Atlanta was a city, landlocked

16:50.143 --> 16:55.347
hundreds of miles from the area
we now call the Atlantic Ocean.

16:55.447 --> 16:59.385
Yet, so desperate the city's
desire for tourism

16:59.485 --> 17:02.522
that they moved offshore,
becoming an island

17:02.621 --> 17:06.526
and an even bigger Delta hub,
until the city overdeveloped

17:06.625 --> 17:09.528
and it started to sink.

17:09.628 --> 17:12.132
Knowing their fate,
the quality people

17:12.231 --> 17:16.068
ran away-- Ted Turner,
Hank Aaron, Jeff Foxworthy

17:16.169 --> 17:19.538
the guy who invented Coca-Cola,
the Magician,

17:19.638 --> 17:23.143
and the other so-called gods
of our legends--

17:23.242 --> 17:25.112
though gods they were...

17:25.211 --> 17:27.480
and also, Jane Fonda was there.

17:27.579 --> 17:31.151
The others chose to remain
behind on their porches

17:31.250 --> 17:35.422
with their rifles, and one day
evolve into mermaids

17:35.521 --> 17:38.990
and sing, and dance,
and ring in the new...

17:39.092 --> 17:40.826
[ All ]
HAIL ATLANTA!

17:40.926 --> 17:43.061
- [ Beeps ]
- "THE MAGICIAN"?

17:43.163 --> 17:45.132
WHOA-WHOA-WHOA!
WOULDN'T IT TAKE
MILLIONS OF YEARS

17:45.231 --> 17:47.267
TO EVOLVE INTO MERMAIDS?

17:47.366 --> 17:48.901
NORMALLY, YES.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.971
BUT THE CAFFEINE
REALLY SPED THINGS UP.

17:52.070 --> 17:53.640
THAT STUFF'S WONDERFUL.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.241
SO, WHEN UMBRIEL

17:55.342 --> 17:57.609
FIRST BROUGHT HOME
THIS CARPETBAGGER

17:57.710 --> 17:58.744
I WAS AGIN' IT

17:58.845 --> 18:01.847
BUT DAMN IF OL' LEGS
HERE AIN'T GROWN ON ME!

18:01.948 --> 18:03.316
AW, SHUCKS, COLONEL.

18:03.415 --> 18:04.317
[ Spitting ]

18:04.416 --> 18:05.317
[ Ding ]

18:05.417 --> 18:06.986
WELL, IT'S ALL
VERY NICE HERE

18:07.086 --> 18:08.320
BUT WE SHOULD BE GOING.

18:08.421 --> 18:09.989
I MISS ME WIFE
AND ME OXYGEN.

18:10.088 --> 18:12.924
YES, WE ALL MISS OUR LOVED ONES
AND GASES.

18:13.025 --> 18:14.661
COME ON, FRY.
WAIT.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.163
I'M NOT GOING WITH YOU.

18:16.262 --> 18:17.364
[ All Gasping ]

18:17.463 --> 18:18.964
BUT, FRY, WHAT ABOUT US?

18:19.065 --> 18:21.334
WHAT ABOUT YOUR LIFE
ON THE SURFACE?

18:21.433 --> 18:23.269
YOU DON'T BELONG DOWN HERE.

18:23.369 --> 18:24.436
SHE'S RIGHT.

18:24.537 --> 18:26.205
I MEAN, SURE,
THEY GOT THE BRAVES

18:26.306 --> 18:28.007
BUT IT'S A THIRD-RATE SYMPHONY.

18:28.106 --> 18:30.710
FRY, YOU HALF-MAD,
HALF-INSANE MANIAC

18:30.809 --> 18:32.511
BE REASONABLE.

18:32.612 --> 18:34.780
DON'T YOU REALIZE THAT
IF YOU STAY AT THIS DEPTH

18:34.881 --> 18:37.849
YOUR BODY WILL PERMANENTLY ADAPT
TO THE PRESSURE?

18:37.950 --> 18:40.019
REALIZE IT?
I DON'T EVEN
UNDERSTAND IT.

18:40.118 --> 18:43.490
IT MEANS YOU'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO RETURN TO THE SURFACE.

18:43.589 --> 18:44.790
I DON'T CARE.
I'M STAYING.

18:44.891 --> 18:46.792
I'VE GOT EVERYTHING
I WANT RIGHT HERE.

18:46.893 --> 18:50.163
I'M BORED!
LET'S GO.

18:51.663 --> 18:52.832
YOU KNOW, FRY

18:52.932 --> 18:55.167
I'VE GOT A LITTLE PLACE
JUST OUTSIDE TOWN.

18:55.268 --> 18:56.736
YOU COULD COME VISIT,
MAYBE?

18:58.471 --> 18:59.572
SORRY, ZOIDBERG.

18:59.672 --> 19:01.307
I'M TRYING TO JOIN
THE COUNTRY CLUB.

19:01.407 --> 19:04.042
[ Sobbing ]
AH, FRY!

19:04.143 --> 19:06.011
[ Blubbering ]

19:06.112 --> 19:07.680
I'LL MISS YOU!

19:07.779 --> 19:11.718
Y'ALL COME BACK, NOW,
YOU HEAR?

19:11.817 --> 19:13.853
LET'S GO, DAMN IT!
LET'S GO!

19:17.390 --> 19:19.759
WELL, I GUESS
THIS IS GOOD-BYE
FOR ME AS WELL.

19:19.858 --> 19:21.027
WHATEVER.
LATER.

19:21.126 --> 19:22.094
BYE.

19:25.397 --> 19:29.201
WHOA! MY HOME!

19:29.301 --> 19:31.671
IT BURNED DOWN!

19:31.770 --> 19:33.339
[ Crying ]

19:33.440 --> 19:35.208
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

19:35.307 --> 19:37.777
THAT'S
A VERY GOOD QUESTION.

19:37.876 --> 19:40.579
SO, THAT'S
WHERE I LEFT MY CIGAR.

19:40.680 --> 19:43.282
THAT JUST RAISES
FURTHER QUESTIONS.

19:43.383 --> 19:45.884
YOU KNOW, UMBRIEL,
THESE LAST 24 HOURS

19:45.984 --> 19:48.587
HAVE BEEN
THE HAPPIEST DAYS OF MY LIFE.

19:48.688 --> 19:53.692
OH, FRY, I WANT YOU TO MAKE
A MER-WOMAN OUT OF MER-ME.

19:56.596 --> 20:00.366
MERCY! I DO BELIEVE
I'M GETTIN' THE VAPORS.

20:01.701 --> 20:05.605
[ Both Moaning ]

20:05.704 --> 20:07.640
[ Umbriel ]
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

20:07.740 --> 20:09.909
YEAH, I'M A LITTLE
CONFUSED, TOO.

20:10.009 --> 20:13.078
HOW DO I... YOU KNOW,
WITH THE TAIL, AND ALL?

20:13.179 --> 20:15.080
I'M NOT YOUR FIRST,
AM I?

20:15.181 --> 20:17.250
I MEAN, I LAY MY EGGS,
THEN I LEAVE

20:17.349 --> 20:19.551
AND YOU RELEASE
YOUR FERTILIZER.

20:19.652 --> 20:20.819
[ Gasping ]

20:20.920 --> 20:22.555
[ Panting ]

20:22.654 --> 20:24.757
WHY COULDN'T SHE BE
THE OTHER KIND OF MERMAID

20:24.856 --> 20:27.660
WITH THE FISH PART ON TOP,
AND THE LADY PART ON THE BOTTOM?

20:28.961 --> 20:32.230
NOW, WHO'S GOING TO ESCORT
ME TO THE DEBUTANTE BALL?

20:32.332 --> 20:35.501
WELL, WHAT ABOUT THAT RICH,
YOUNG DUGONG FROM MACON?

20:36.836 --> 20:39.838
THERE. THE ENGINE MODIFICATIONS
ARE COMPLETE.

20:39.939 --> 20:41.240
PREPARE FOR LAUNCH.

20:41.340 --> 20:44.510
[ Engines Roaring ]

20:46.746 --> 20:50.115
WAIT! WAIT FOR ME!
DON'T LEAVE ME HERE!

20:50.215 --> 20:51.150
[ Gasping ]

20:52.652 --> 20:55.521
[ Grunting ]

20:58.190 --> 21:00.460
AH!

21:00.559 --> 21:01.693
[ Screaming ]

21:04.130 --> 21:06.265
[ Man ]
AND, SO

21:06.365 --> 21:09.469
IN HONOR
OF HIS RECORD-BREAKING CATCH

21:09.568 --> 21:13.605
I'M PROUD TO AWARD BENDER
THIS CHECK FOR $1,000.

21:13.705 --> 21:15.307
[ Crowd Cheering ]

21:15.407 --> 21:16.608
[ Grunting ]

21:16.709 --> 21:17.844
[ Gasping ]

21:17.943 --> 21:20.446
IT'S YOU!
HEY, BUDDY!

21:20.547 --> 21:21.647
MY MANWICH!

21:21.748 --> 21:24.049
FRY, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:24.150 --> 21:25.518
WHAT ABOUT UMBRIEL?

21:25.617 --> 21:29.154
WELL, IT TURNS OUT I LOVED HER,
BUT I WASN'T "IN LOVE" WITH HER.

21:29.255 --> 21:30.823
TROUBLE IN BED.

21:30.923 --> 21:33.192
AH, IT'S GREAT
TO HAVE YOU BACK, BUDDY.

21:33.291 --> 21:34.461
WAIT, UH...

21:34.560 --> 21:36.028
THIS IS NO RECORD.

21:36.127 --> 21:37.963
GIVE ME BACK THAT CHECK.

21:38.064 --> 21:40.700
I'M GIVING IT
TO SOME GIANT ORPHANS.

21:40.799 --> 21:43.035
OW! BENDER,
YOU'RE HURTING ME!

21:43.134 --> 21:46.739
OW!
[ Choking ]

21:46.838 --> 21:49.842
HEY!
I'M TRYING TO SLEEP IN HERE.

21:49.942 --> 21:52.845
[ Donovan ]
HAIL ATLANTA.
